title: For Sale:  Law Enforcement Members - Free NO CHARGE Firearms Transfers
location: Arnold, Jefferson County, St. Louis, Missouri
postcontent:
Active Duty Law Enforcement members (federal, state & local) receive free, no charge transfers for up to five (5) incoming personal firearm transfers per year.  Duty Weapons are transferred for free with no limit (requires letter from CLEO or authorized authority). 
Senior Citizens age 65 and above incoming transfers are only $10 each firearm, no limit.
I am a home-based FFL in Arnold, Missouri and am available by appointment only.  My preferred method of communication is through the "Contact Seller" link on this page. I will then reply or I will call you if you leave a phone number. 
All other incoming transfers are $35 for the first gun and no charge for each additional firearm transferred at the same time up to a total of 3 firearms. $10 for each additional firearm over three.
On occasion I offer firearms for sale, so take a look at my listings to see what I might have today.  It is not required or necessary for you to come to me for a purchase of one of my items, if you choose I will ship to your FFL in the St. Louis metro area for free (you will be responsible for any transfer fees at the other FFL dealer). All of my pricing is "out the door pricing" which includes the sales tax which I am required to charge.  I can ship anywhere in the lower 48 states for $20 (handgun) or $30 (long gun) to wherever the firearm is legal to own. 
I also accept Curio and Relic Collector's FFL licenses for deliveries directly to the C&R holder. Free delivery in the St. Louis metro area. 
I accept cash, U.S. Postal Money Orders, and credit cards (5% fee added for credit card payments). 
All Transactions are private and discreet, and all firearms laws will be obeyed and followed.
By Appointment Only.
